  </figcaption>
</figure></action-text-attachment><br><br>The point itself is a sheer, straight drop-off of like 3000 feet.&nbsp; No pictures do justice to how nervous this whole situation made me.&nbsp; I'm not a big fan of heights.<br><br><action-text-attachment sgid="BAh7CEkiCGdpZAY6BkVUSSJXZ2lkOi8vYW4tZXZlbnQvQWN0aXZlU3RvcmFnZTo6QmxvYi85ODkwOTE5Mi01OGI4LTQ3MWQtYmE5ZC0xYTg4MmEzMWI3NzM_ZXhwaXJlc19pbgY7AFRJIgxwdXJwb3NlBjsAVEkiD2F0dGFjaGFibGUGOwBUSSIPZXhwaXJlc19hdAY7AFQw--1824344162db7a1404f1cc195437879505853d22" content-type="image/jpeg" url="https://www.carrie-truman.fyi/rails/active_storage/blobs/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaEpJaWs1T0Rrd09URTVNaTAxT0dJNExUUTNNV1F0WW1FNVpDMHhZVGc0TW1Fek1XSTNOek1HT2daRlZBPT0iLCJleHAiOm51bGwsInB1ciI6ImJsb2JfaWQifX0=--72a13868ef1585eb6d89bda0911771fce8a2c335/IMG_2920.jpg" filename="IMG_2920.jpg" filesize="256712" width="640" height="480" previewable="true" presentation="gallery" caption="just straight down if you look over this cliff"><figure class="attachment attachment--preview attachment--jpg">
